      "writtenOn": "2020-09-24T22:47:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The new fields should not introduce compatibility issues with older studio versions(see https://developers.google.com/protocol-buffers/docs/overview#updating):\n\nAny new fields that you add should be optional or repeated. This means that any messages serialized by code using your \"old\" message format can be parsed by your new generated code, as they won\u0027t be missing any required elements. You should set up sensible default values for these elements so that new code can properly interact with messages generated by old code.\n\nNote the in Proto3 all fields are optional by default.\n\nI\u0027m not too concerned about calculating the disk size, for the following reasons:\n\n- It is unlikely that users will have a larger number of snapshots (We likely would have to change our UI design if we expect large number of snapshots)\n- The folder (should) only contain 5 entries.\n- The performance problem would still remain if you query with a filter for \"disksize\"\n\nIf it turns out that calculating size is prohibitively expensive we can calculate the disk size when we are writing out the snapshot and store it in the snapshot description protobuf.\n\nI would prefer not to add support for filtering, as this requires us to provide some form of selection mechanism (easy to do wrong and hard to extend if we miss something).",
